<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     10-19 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bradley-Steck Named Pittsburgh Correspondent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tara Bradley-Steck, a newswoman in the
Pittsburgh bureau of The Associated Press since 1984, has been
named correspondent in charge.
   The appointment was announced Thursday by Philadelphia Chief of
Bureau George Zucker. Bradley-Steck succeeds Peter Mattiace, who
recently was named AP's bureau chief in Charleston, W.Va.
   Bradley-Steck, 34, joined the AP in Pittsburgh, her hometown.
She is a graduate of Bryn Mawr College and previously worked for
VISTA in Montana, where she edited an Indian reservation newspaper,
and for the Beaver County Times in Beaver, Pa.
</TEXT>
