<FIRST>r a AM-AstaireSuit     10-19 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Astaire Suit,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fred Astaire's Widow Sues Columbia Over Film Distribution</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The widow of actor Fred Astaire has filed
suit against Columbia Pictures Entertainment over distribution of
royalties from two of his films.
   In a suit filed Wednesday in Superior Court, Robyn Astaire
claims Columbia owes her at least $25,000 in receipts from the
films ``You'll Never Get Rich'' and ``You Were Never Lovelier,'' in
which the famous dancer starred.
   She also seeks Columbia's accounting records regarding the
films' distribution.
   Mrs. Astaire alleges that since at least 1987, Columbia has
breached a contract under which Astaire was to receive 5 percent of
all net receipts in excess of $100,000 up to $5,000 and 10 percent
of all net receipts in excess of $200,000.
   Mrs. Astaire's attorney, Joseph F. Hart, said Thursday his
client does not know exactly how much money she is owed because
Columbia has refused to provide accounting records to her.
   He said the amount Columbia owes Mrs. Astaire may be
significantly higher than $25,000.
   Columbia officials could not be reached for comment after
business hours late Thursday.
</TEXT>
