<HEAD>New Endowment Chief Eases Tension With Congress</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The new chairman of the National Endowment for
the Arts says he's begun to calm a congressional uproar over
obscenity and vows to seek greater financial support for the arts,
including a possible appeal to millionaire rock stars for donations.
   John E. Frohnmayer told reporters Wednesday he had met twice
recently with Sen. Jesse Helms, R-N.C., the endowment's harshest
