<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``It looked like a snake hacked with an ax. It was in bits and
pieces.'' _ Sen. Alan Cranston, D-Calif., after flying over a
section of highway that collapsed during Tuesday's Norther
California earthquake.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``After 25 years of public neglect, Medicaid is nothing short of
Uncle Sam's poor stepchild.'' _ Jon E. Vice, chairman of the
National Association of Children's Hospitals and Related
Institutions in asserting that more than half of the nation's
children slip through the program's safety net.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``Analysis breeds paralysis.'' _ A report by Congress' Office of
Technology Assessment that calls for a major overhaul of the
Superfund and says that more than half of the multi-billion dollar
program is being spent on studies, management and ineffective
technology instead of cleaning up toxic waste dumps.

