<HEAD>List Of Nobel Winners In Literature</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the Nobel Prize for Literature winners. There
were no prizes awarded in 1914, 1918, 1935, 1940, 1941, 1942 and
1943.
   1989: Camilo Jose Cela, (1916- ), Spanish.
   1988: Naguib Mahfouz, (1912- ), Egyptian.
   1987: Joseph Brodsky, (1940- ), Russian-American.
   1986: Wole Soyinka (1934- ), Nigerian.
   1985: Claude Simon (1913- ), French.
   1984: Jaroslav Seifert (1901-1985), Czech.
   1983: William Golding (1911- ), British.
   1982: Gabriel Garcia Marquez (1928- ), Colombian.
   1981: Elias Canetti (1905- ), Bulgarian.
   1980: Czeslaw Milosz (1911- ), Polish-American.
   1979: Odysseus Elytis (1911- ), Greek.
   1978: Isaac Bashevis Singer (1904- ), American (born in Poland).
   1977: Vincente Aleixandre (1898-1984), Spanish.
   1976: Saul Bellow (1915- ), American.
   1975: Eugenio Montale (1896-1981), Italian.
   1974: Eyvind Johnson (1900-76), Swedish.
   Harry Edmund Martinson (1904-78), Swedish.
   1973: Patrick White (1912- ), Australian.
   1972: Heinrich Boell (1917-85), German.
   1971: Pablo Neruda (1904-73), Chilean.
   1970: Alexander Solzhenitsyn (1919- ), Russian.
   1969: Samuel Beckett (1906- ), Anglo-French (born in Ireland).
   1968: Yasunari Kawabata (1899-1972), Japanese.
   1967: Miguel Angel Asturias (1899-1974), Guatemalan.
   1966: Samuel Joseph Agnon (1888-1970), Israeli (born in Poland).
   Nelly Sachs (1891-1970), Swedish (born in Germany).
   1965: Mikhail A. Sholokhov (1905-84), Russian.
   1964: Jean-Paul Sartre (1905-80), French (award declined).
   1963: George Seferis (1900-71), Greek.
   1962: John Steinbeck (1902-68), American.
   1961: Ivo Andric (1892-1975), Yugoslav.
   1960: Saint-John Perse (1887-1975), French.
   1959: Salvatore Quasimodo (1901-68), Italian.
   1958: Boris L. Pasternak (1890-1960), Russian (award declined).
   1957: Albert Camus (1913-60), French.
   1956: Juan Ramon Jimenez (1881-1958), Spanish.
   1955: Halldor K. Laxness (1902- ), Icelandic.
   1954: Ernest Hemingway (1899-1961), American.
   1953: Sir Winston Churchill (1874-1965), British.
   1952: Francois Mauriac (1885-1970), French.
   1951: Par F. Lagerkvist (1891-1974), Swedish.
   1950: Bertrand A. W. Russell (1872-1970), British.
   1949: William Faulkner (1897-1962), American.
   1948: T.S. Eliot (1888-1965), British (born in the United
States).
   1947: Andre Gide (1869-1951), French.
   1946: Hermann Hesse (1877-1962), Swiss (born in Germany).
   1945: Gabriela Mistral (1889-1957), Chilean.
   1944: Johannes V. Jensen (1873-1950), Danish.
   1939: Frans E. Sillanpaa (1888-1964), Finnish.
   1938: Pearl S. Buck (1892-1973), American.
   1937: Roger Martin du Gard (1881-1958), French.
   1936: Eugene O'Neill (1888-1953), American.
   1934: Luigi Pirandello (1867-1936), Italian.
   1933: Ivan A. Bunin (1870-1953), French (born in Russia).
   1932: John Galsworthy (1867-1933), British.
   1931: Erik A. Karlfeldt (1864-1931), Swedish (awarded
posthumously).
   1930: Sinclair Lewis (1885-1951), American.
   1929: Thomas Mann (1875-1955), German.
   1928: Sigrid Undset (1882-1949), Norwegian (born in Denmark).
   1927: Henri Bergson (1859-1941), French.
   1926: Grazia Deledda (1875-1936), Italian.
   1925: George Bernard Shaw (1856-1950), British (born in Ireland).
   1924: Ladislaus S. Reymont (1868-1925), Polish.
   1923: William Butler Yeats (1865-1939), Irish.
   1922: Jacinto Benavente y Martinez (1866-1954), Spanish.
