<FIRST>r w PM-FEMA-Telephones     10-19 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-FEMA-Telephones,120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Emergency Agency Opening Telephone Lines for Earthquake Victims</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Federal Emergency Management Agency said
today that it will open 100 toll-free telephone lines for
earthquake disaster victims in California.
   The telephone lines will allow disaster victims to make requests
from FEMA for emergency needs, such as housing, money or food.
   Gregg Chappell, FEMA's associate director, said inspectors will
visit disaster victims after receiving their calls for help. The
telephone lines are a stopgap measure until FEMA opens disaster
application offices in seven California counties, he said.
   ``This is a way to get in front of the process,'' he said.
   The telephone number is 1-800-4629029. The hundred telephone
lines will be open 24 hours a day, starting at 10 a.m. EDT.
</TEXT>
