<SECOND>PM-Son Slashed,0261</SECOND>
<HEAD>Police: Mother Arrested for Slashing Son, Rubbing Salt in Wounds</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANDERSON, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mother has been arrested on charges she
cut up her teen-age son with a shard of glass and rubbed salt in
the wounds to drive ``evil spirits'' from him, police said.
   Virginia Patterson Jenkins, 37, of Anderson, was charged with
assault and battery of a high and aggravated nature Monday. She
remained jailed today without bond.
   She was arrested after a neighbor reported that Ms. Jenkins'
14-year-old son, who was beaten and bleeding, sought refuge at his
house Monday night, said sheriff's Deputy Mike Temple.
   Temple said the boy had cuts all over his body from a piece of
broken mirror and salt was rubbed into his wounds. The boy also had
been forced to drink salt water, he said.
   ``This woman thought the boy was possessed and enlisted the help
of her 12-year-old son to exorcise it,'' Temple said. ``This is one
of the most bizarre cases I've ever seen.''
   The 12-year-old apparently helped hold his brother down during
the attack, said Sheriff's Capt. John Skipper.
   The 14-year-old was taken to Anderson Memorial Hospital, where
he spent Monday night, then was taken into protective custody and
placed in foster care along with his younger brother, Temple said.
Skipper said there were no other siblings and that the boys' father
did not live in the area.
   All the mirrors but one were broken in Ms. Jenkins' home and
deputies confiscated a bloody shower curtain, Temple said.
