<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Acting loud and weird is OK, said actress Julia
Roberts, as long as that's what you really are.
   ``I think I'm loud and weird,'' Roberts said in the November
issue of Cosmopolitan. ``But if you're a real person, people can't
help but respond in the same manner.''
   She said she believes in speaking her mind.
   ``I find myself becoming more open and honest,'' she said.
``Still, I know that's a great risk to take. But I've found that if
I say what I'm feeling, 90 percent of the time it can be worked
out.''
   Roberts, 23, whose brother is actor Eric Roberts, names her
heroines as actresses Faye Dunaway, Lauren Bacall and Rita Hayworth
_ ``women who have (guts), women with definite ideas.''
   Roberts is known for her role as Daisy Araujo in last year's
film ``Mystic Pizza,'' playing a sultry young woman chafing at the
confines of a Connecticut fishing village.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prince Charles and Princess Diana will make their
first visit to Nigeria and Cameroon in mid-March, Buckingham Palace
announced Thursday.
   The Prince and Princess of Wales are going to the West African
nations at the invitation of both governments, the palace said.
Dates of the visits had not been set.
   Charles' parents, Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip, visited
Nigeria in 1956.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bill Cosby is helping South Carolina
victims of Hurricane Hugo with a benefit concert in December.
   The University of South Carolina is underwriting the Dec. 1 show
at the school's Carolina Coliseum.
   Cosby volunteered because of his ``close friendship'' with the
university, the school's president, James Holderman, said
Wednesday. Cosby is waiving his artist's fee and expenses.
   Cosby was awarded an honorary doctor of humane letters degree
from the university in 1986, when he gave the commencement address.
   About 10,000 seats will be available for the concert. Tickets go
on sale Monday and will cost $10 and $15.
