<SECOND>AM-Cheney-Trip,130</SECOND>
<HEAD>US Defense Secretary To Visit Europe, Australia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Defense Secratary Dick Cheney begins a 21-day
trip on Saturday that will take him to several European nations and
Australia, the Pentagon announced on Thursday.
   Cheney plans to meet with his counterparts during stops in
France, Britain, West Germany, and Italy, and attend the NATO
Nuclear Planning Group meeting in Portugal scheduled for Oct. 23-25.
   He will also meet with U.S. servicemen and women deployed in the
Mediterranean, West Germany, Britain and the Pacific, the Pentagon
said in a statement.
   In Australia, Cheney will participate with Secretary of State
James A. Baker III in the annual U.S.-Australian bilateral meetings.
   The defense secretary is also scheduled to consult with Adm.
Huntington Hardisty while in Honolulu, the statement said.
</TEXT>
