<FIRST>r a AM-SkinheadBeating     10-19 0247</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Skinhead Beating,0254</SECOND>
<HEAD>Skinhead Sentenced in Racist Beating</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A white-supremacist ``skinhead'' was
sentenced to up to 20 years in prison Thursday for helping beat a
black immigrant to death.
   Multnomah County Circuit Judge Robert Redding sentenced Kyle H.
Brewster, 19, of Portland to 10 to 20 years on one count of
first-degree manslaughter in the November slaying of Mulegta Seraw,
said Redding's law clerk, Jon Ghastin.
   Seraw, a 27-year-old Ethiopian, was killed near his home last
November by three neo-Nazi racists, police said.
   Brewster pleaded guilty Sept. 1 to the manslaughter charge, one
count of first-degree assault and three charges of intimidation.
   He was sentenced to 10 years on the assault charge and five
years each on two of the intimidation charges. The sentences were
to run concurrently with the manslaughter sentence.
   One of the other men involved in the attack, Kenneth Mieske, 23,
admitted beating Seraw with a baseball bat, and pleaded guilty to
murder. He was sentenced to life in prison June 5.
   The third man, Steven Strasser, 20, is awaiting trial.
   Police said the three were members of a neo-Nazi, white
supremacist gang called East Side White Pride. Portland is a
stronghold for white-supremacist gangs, according to a federal
prosecutor.
   The skinhead subculture, so-called because its members sport
severely short haircuts, originated in London in the 1960s.
Segments of the movement took on Nazi overtones in recent years,
and since have been supported by and associated with
white-supremacist groups.
</TEXT>
