<HEAD>Earthquake By The Numbers</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-SF Quake Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here's a by-the-numbers look at earthquake information.
   Corporate donations other than money: 15,000-20,000 T-shirts,
jackets, sweatshirts and sweaters; 55,000 gallons of water in
generic white cans.
   California National Guardsmen called up for duty: 1,173.
   Aftershocks since 5:04 p.m. Tuesday: more than 1,400.
   Length of the quake: 15 seconds.
   Length of collapsed section of San Francisco-Oakland Bay Bridge:
50 feet.
   Length of collapsed Nimitz Freeway (Interstate 880): 1\ miles,
18 blocks.
   Length of time it will take to repair: 18 months.
   Bridges being inspected within 50 miles of quake epicenter:
1,500.
   Rooms now available at the Fairmont Hotel on Nob Hill: 450.
   Messages on CompuServe and Prodigy computer earthquake forums:
1,960.
   People without electricity after the quake: 1,000,000.
