<HEAD>22 Killed in Tour Bus Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A head-on collision before dawn Friday
between a tourist bus and a tractor-trailer in far northern New
South Wales left at least 22 people dead, police said.
   At least 22 other passengers on the bus were injured, many
seriously, in the 4 a.m. accident, which occurred on the Pacific
Highway a mile outside the town of Cowper, police said.
   The tourist coach, operated by Sunliner Coaches of Sydney, was
en route from Sydney to Brisbane when it collided with the
tractor-trailer, whose driver was instantly killed, police said.
   Rescue helicopters came from Brisbane and the Gold Coast to take
the most seriously injured to Brisbane, the closest large city with
facilities to treat the victims, authorities said.
   It was not immediately known whether any foreigners were on
board the bus.
