<HEAD>Thousands Die Yearly Because They Skipped Vaccines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thousands of deaths occur each year among
Americans who have not received their recommended vaccines, federal
health officials warned Thursday.
   The national Centers for Disease Control, in its weekly report,
noted that more than 40,000 excess flu-related deaths have occurred
in each of several influenza epidemics in recent years. An
estimated 300,000 new hepatitis B cases occur each year, and the
incidence of measles and mumps is on the rise in young adults.
   ``Safe and effective vaccines are available for all these
diseases,'' the CDC said.
   The CDC's report called attention to next week's designation as
the fourth annual National Adult Immunization Awareness Week.
