<FIRST>r f PM-Diamond-StarJapan     10-19 0186</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Diamond-Star Japan,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Diamond-Star Cars Head to Japan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORMAL, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first Diamond-Star Motors Corp. cars
bound for sale in Japan are expected to roll off the assembly line
next week, said officials who gathered to celebrate the company's
first Japanese exports.
   ``We're excited and proud that cars manufactured and assembled
in Illinois will now be sold in Mitsubishi showrooms in Japan,''
said Diamond-Star Chairman Lino Piedra.
   Diamond-Star, a joint venture of Chrysler Motors and Mitsubishi
Motors, will produce about 1,500 Mitsubishi Eclipse automobiles for
export to Japan by year's end, the company said Wednesday.
   ``Exporting cars to Japan represents a major milestone for both
the workers of Diamond-Star and our parent companies,'' Piedra said
in a news release.
   A spokeswoman for Diamond-Star conceded that the 1,500 cars
bound for Japan represent a very small percentage of the 52,000
cars produced at the plant so far this year, but said the company
hopes to build its exports.
   ``Probably the number we're going to produce this year (for
Japan) is not a large amount,'' said spokeswoman Robin Skiles.
``But we have to start somewhere.''
</TEXT>
