<HEAD>London Stocks Advance in Light Trading</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with later trading.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices advanced in modest trading Thursday,
boosted largely by technical factors linked to a squeeze among
investors shopping for blue chip stocks.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was up 16.1
points, or 0.7 percent, at 2,186.2 at midday.
