<HEAD>IBM, Digital Equipment Join Network Standards Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The world's two largest computer companies have
become voting members of a standard-setting organization for
telecommunications networks, it was announced Thursday.
   The voting membership of International Business Machines Corp.
and Digital Equipment Corp. should help the group settle on
standards so customers can be sure the devices they use to run
their phone and computer networks work together smoothly.
   The group, the OSI Network Management Forum, was founded last
year by several leading companies including American Telephone &amp;
Telegraph Co., British Telecom PLC, Northern Telecom Ltd., Unisys
Corp. and Hewlett-Packard Co.
