<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed firmer Thursday in thin
dealings driven largely by technical factors and underlying support
from sharp gains on Wall Street.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 19.2
points, or 0.8 percent, to 2,189.3.
   The Financial Times 30-share index ended the day 13.6 points
higher at 1,772.1.
   Volume continued to fall off. Total turnover was 382.9 million
shares, down from 449.3 million on Wednesday.
