<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Grace     10-19 0270</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Grace,0281</SECOND>
<HEAD>Profit Doubles in 3rd Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   W.R. Grace &amp; Co. said Thursday its third-quarter
profit nearly doubled because of a large gain on the restructuring
of its energy operations.
   Grace, whose main business is specialty chemicals but which also
has interests in manufacturing and health care services, said it
earned $97.9 million, or $1.15 a share, in the three months ended
Sept. 30, up 93.7 percent from $50.5 million, or 60 cents a share,
a year earlier.
   Third-quarter revenue rose 7 percent to $1.49 billion from $1.39
billion a year earlier.
   The latest results included a pretax gain of $114.4 million
resulting from the energy operations restructuring. That included
the sale of Grace Equipment Co., an initial public offering in
Grace Energy Corp. and an adjustment in the carrying value of
natural resource assts.
   The latest results were also depressed by higher interest
expenses and an accrual for stock appreciation rights.
   In its specialty chemicals business, Grace said reported
operating income after taxes of $59 million for the quarter,
slightly ahead of 1988 results.
   Operating income for the quarter rose 22 percent to $9.2 million
in natural resoruces, fell 14 percent to $7.6 million in health
care and dropped 29.6 percent in specialty businesses to $8.8
million due to absence of a $4.6 million gain a year earlier.
   For the first nine months of the year, Grace earned $171.4
million, or $2.01 a share, up 8.4 percent from $158.1 million, or
$1.87 a share, a year earlier.
   Revenue rose 6.3 percent to $4.4 billion for the nine months
from $4.13 billion a year earlier.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
