<FIRST>d f AM-EvansvilleNewspapers     10-19 0185</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Evansville Newspapers,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tuley Takes Over JOA Management for Evansville Newspapers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thomas W. Tuley, editor and president of
The Evansville Courier, will take over management of The Evansville
Courier Co., which also serves as business agent for The Evansville
Press.
   The Courier, owned by Scripps Howard Newspapers, and The Press,
owned by Robert H. Hartmann, maintain separate editorial
departments, but the advertising, circulation and production
functions are combined under a Joint Operating Agreement.
   Since 1986, Tully and Hartmann have shared management of the
business departments of the newspapers.
   Hartmann announced Wednesday he would step down as chairman of
the JOA's management committee at the end of the year.
   Tuley will assume full responsibility for the management
arrangement on Jan. 1 in addition to continuing his duties as
editor of The Courier. Hartman will continue as publisher of The
Press.
   Tuley, 49, has been editor and president of The Courier since
Scripps Howard purchased the newspaper in 1986. He was editor of
The Press from 1983 to 1986, prior to Scripps Howard's sale of The
Press and acquisition of The Courier.
</TEXT>
