<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Gillette     10-19 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Gillette,0200</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gillette Reports 2 Percent Growth In Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gillette Co. reported Thursday its earnings grew 2
percent in the third quarter compared with the same period a year
ago, as sales rose by more than $70 million.
   Gillette, which controls about 60 percent of the world market in
razors, had net income of $65.2 million for the quarter ended Sept.
30, compared with $63.9 million for the third quarter of 1988.
Earnings per share were the same in both quarters, 57 cents.
   Sales for the third quarter totaled $921.6 million, compared
with $845.7 million in the year-ago period.
   For the first nine months of the year, net income was down
slightly, from $207 million, or $1.82 a share, in 1988 to $205.3
million, or $2.02 a share, this year. Sales for the first nine
months of 1989 totaled $2.76 billion, compared with $2.61 billion
in the same period last year.
   Earlier this month Gillette introduced a new razor, called
Sensor, which will go on sale next year. The razor will be priced
higher than the company's current brands, and Gillette officials
hope the product will yield more profits.
</TEXT>
